data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Cotton Ride
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.

data.flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Fluffy Tag
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. During your next turn, the attacks of that Pokémon do 40 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

data.flavorText: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Helping Hand
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Cotton Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Encore
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can only use that attack.

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Windy Mischief
attacks.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Light Steps
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Triple Draw
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Flying Fury
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokémon Tools from your Pokémon. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

data.flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: The Wages of Fluff
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out during your next turn, take 2 more Prize cards.

data.flavorText: It rides on the wind and slips into people's homes. After it has turned a room into a cotton-filled mess, it giggles to itself and takes off.

data.name: Whimsicott

attacks.name: Sneaky Pocket
attacks.text: Put a card from your hand in the Lost Zone. If you do, draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Lost March
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon, except p (Prism Star) Pokémon, in the Lost Zone.

data.flavorText: This nuisance sneaks into people's homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.

data.name: Whimsicott-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Fluffy Cotton
abilities.text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

attacks.name: Energy Blow
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Toy Box-GX
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 5 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

data.flavorText: As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.
